trigger_prototype.name: Innodb Buffer Pool Instances is too small
trigger_prototype.description: If you are using MySQL 5.5 and higher you should use several Innodb Buffer Pool Instances for performance reasons. Some rules are: Innodb Buffer Pool Instance should be at least 1 Gbyte in size. Innodb Buffer Pool Instances you can set equal to the number of cores of your machine.

trigger_prototype.name: Innodb Deadlock detected
trigger_prototype.description: You got an Innodb Deadlock. Please talk to your development department to fix this. Deadlocks are an application problem!

trigger_prototype.name: Innodb Flush Log at Transaction Commit
trigger_prototype.description: Innodb Flush Log at Transaction Commit is set to a values != 1. This can lead to a loss of commited transactions in case of a power failure.

trigger_prototype.name: Innodb Force Recovery is enabled
trigger_prototype.description: Innodb Force Recovery is enabled. This mode should be used for data recovery purposes only. It prohibits writing to the data.

trigger_prototype.name: Innodb Foreign Key error detected
trigger_prototype.description: You got an Innodb Foreign Key error. Please talk to your development department to fix this.

trigger_prototype.name: Innodb Log File size is too small
trigger_prototype.description: The Innodb Log File size is possibly too small. Choosing a small Innodb Log File size can have significant performance impacts.
